# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# prefabs.def  -  "drop-in" designs for enemies, weapons and props
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Each line defines a named design as keyword/value pairs. Omitted keys keep
# their defaults. Maps and the in-game editor place these by name, so adding a
# new design here makes it immediately available without touching any code.
#
#   enemy  <name> material <m> radius <r> speed <s> hp <n>
#   weapon <name> material <m> size <s> damage <n> label <text>
#   prop   <name> shape <box|sphere> material <m> size <s>
#
# `material` refers to a name from materials.def.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

# --- Enemies (rendered as shootable spheres; speed drifts them at you) ---
enemy grunt   material enemy  radius 0.45 speed 1.4 hp 1
enemy brute   material enemy2 radius 0.70 speed 0.8 hp 3
enemy sniper  material chrome radius 0.40 speed 0.0 hp 1

# --- Weapons (rendered as pickup boxes) ---
weapon pistol  material weapon size 0.30 damage 1 label Pistol
weapon shotgun material weapon size 0.45 damage 3 label Shotgun

# --- Props (static set dressing; boxes also collide) ---
prop crate    shape box    material crate  size 1.0
prop barrel   shape sphere material accent size 1.0
prop pillar   shape box    material mirror size 1.2
prop orb      shape sphere material chrome size 0.8
